</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-67_"><b>Infants and young children</b> - Their higher metabolic rate and less efficient heat regulation put them at higher risk.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-69_"><b>Individuals with chronic illnesses</b> - Conditions like heart disease, diabetes, and respiratory disorders decrease the body's ability to cope with heat stress.
